description.narrative: This programme is based on solid experiences and lessons learned from previous programme interventions. The objective of the programme is to contribute to Zimbabwe's transition into a multi-party democracy, respectful of human rights and a thriving economy benefitting all Zimbabweans. The programme has three main areas of focus, namely: Democratic and accountable governance; Infrastructure rehabilitation and policy development, and; Private sector development in agriculture. As such, the programme in relation to governance will support access to justice for all Zimbabweans, facilitate the transition to more democratic and accountable governance and contribute towards the elimination of gender based violence. Within infrastructure, the programme will support the conduct of transformative public policy analyses as well as the rehabilitation of prioritised infrastructure, resulting in improvements in the living conditions for the general population. In agriculture, the programme is aimed at revitalising the sector through the provision of a credit facility and capacity building. The programme also encompasses support to business advocacy development for the private sector in general.
